Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.97,0:02:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The curry's done.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:47.64,0:02:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.06,0:02:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was gonna die of starvation.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.31,0:02:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This looks great.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:53.31,0:02:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's cold!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.07,0:02:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I made chilled curry this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:56.23,0:02:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's just gotten cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.15,0:03:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I put a lot of time and effort into this.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.28,0:03:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to dissolve the soup \Nstock and the curry powder
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.66,0:03:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and put in a bunch of meat and onions.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.74,0:03:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a lot of work.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.65,0:03:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Mashiro, have some curry.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.20,0:03:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to eat?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.55,0:03:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'll have some.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.00,0:03:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Miho said she got another new part.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.92,0:03:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? That's great.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.46,0:03:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like she's doing well.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.13,0:03:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a message about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.89,0:03:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mashiro, at least stop while you're eating.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.01,0:03:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow is the deadline.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.67,0:03:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He's gotta finish up by the end of the day.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.97,0:03:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But we just had midterms and there \Nhaven't been any holidays lately.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.42,0:03:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't even extend the deadline by one day?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.02,0:03:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A deadline's a deadline.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.19,0:03:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You got into the contest, but you \Ncan't relax and celebrate, can you?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.32,0:03:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.62,0:03:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I just realized we're going to be in Jack.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.31,0:03:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When I imagine not getting any votes and \Nnot getting first in the "Golden Future Cup,"
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.11,0:03:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I get really nervous.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.58,0:03:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The winner is determined based on \Nwho's is the most interesting, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.00,0:03:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How many other series are there?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.38,0:03:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I forgot to ask.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.88,0:04:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I call Hattori and ask?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.64,0:04:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.38,0:04:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We can ask him tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.76,0:04:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you'll make it in time?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:05.30,0:04:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as I don't sleep.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.47,0:04:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you don't sleep?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.68,0:04:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say you didn't \Nsleep at all yesterday, too?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.90,0:04:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't either.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.68,0:04:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a mangaka means dedicating \Nyourself to drawing, even if it kills you.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.02,0:04:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I didn't think I was gonna make it.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.10,0:04:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.07,0:04:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.03,0:04:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What this?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.64,0:04:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say you didn't \Nlike Koogy not too long ago?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.37,0:04:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I guess he is pretty cool after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.87,0:04:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm actually going to his concert tonight.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.74,0:04:34.37,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.00,0:04:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you think about what to do for the next chapter?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.37,0:04:35.94,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,How'd you get tickets?!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.94,0:04:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A little bit.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.13,0:04:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have something ready by the end of the day.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.16,0:04:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.97,0:04:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.26,0:04:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We've still got three months left until the results \Nof the "Golden Future Cup" are announced.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.10,0:04:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've got to do a 19 page \Nchapter every two weeks until then.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.77,0:04:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That means six more chapters.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.94,0:05:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can't do at least that much,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.27,0:05:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,then there's no way we'll be able to keep \Nup a serialization while still in high school.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.71,0:05:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.74,0:05:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already made it this far, so we can't—
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.20,0:05:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Nakai?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.38,0:05:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.50,0:05:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean that really good \Nassistant you were talking about?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.13,0:05:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.92,0:05:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who was crying \Nabout wanting to get serialized?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.63,0:05:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well it sure looks like spring has come.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.34,0:05:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's probably just a meeting or something.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.42,0:05:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think somebody that young \Nand cute could be an editor, do you?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.07,0:05:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, \Nshe does kinda look like Iwase.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.35,0:05:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.80,0:05:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.52,0:05:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mashiro?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:35.18,0:05:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Long time, no see.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:35.89,0:05:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap, he saw us.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.64,0:05:38.74,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,You here for a meeting about the "Golden Future Cup?"
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.10,0:05:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that bad?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.44,0:05:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, it just is.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.32,0:05:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.07,0:05:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got a meeting at six.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.52,0:05:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Six?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.44,0:05:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You still have about 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.24,0:05:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you join us for a bit?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.27,0:05:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do you not want to talk \Nto a "Golden Future Cup" rival?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.91,0:05:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.00,0:05:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You got accepted, too?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.50,0:05:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me introduce you.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.82,0:06:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the runner-up in last \Nyear's "Story King," Aoki Ko.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:03.59,0:06:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,She's didn't have anybody to do the art for her,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.09,0:06:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so I agreed to draw it for \Nthe "Golden Future Cup."
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.47,0:06:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been looking for somebody to do the drawings \Nfor the runner up in the latest "Story King."
Dialogue: 10,0:06:15.89,0:06:16.73,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.73,0:06:19.15,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,This is Mashiro. We worked together on "Crow"
Dialogue: 10,0:06:17.23,0:06:18.90,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,So that's who she is.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.15,0:06:21.11,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,for a little while and I taught him all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.11,0:06:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh—
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.27,0:06:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I really did learn a lot working with Nakai.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.15,0:06:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, stop it.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.53,0:06:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would make you Mashiro's partner?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.93,0:06:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Takagi.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.33,0:06:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.54,0:06:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These two are Ashirogi Muto.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.75,0:06:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're Ashirogi?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.42,0:06:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You did "Money and Intelligence."
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.54,0:06:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think it was any good.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.51,0:06:48.27,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,She sure is blunt.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.70,0:06:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't feel like it should \Nbe in a shounen magazine.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.30,0:06:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was too serious.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.64,0:06:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but what kind \Nof stories do you write?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.80,0:06:58.39,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Don't go getting angry.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.94,0:07:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had to categorize them, I \Nwould have to say they are fantasy.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.56,0:07:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I was writing for a shoujo \Nmagazine called Magnolia,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:10.49,TLNote,,0,0,0,,Note: "Magnolia" refers to "Margaret," Shueisha's bi-weekly shoujo magazine.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.82,0:07:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but they told me that a fantasy like this \Nwas better suited to a shounen magazine.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.56,0:07:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.36,0:07:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't say anything about the story yet, \Nbut it's a good, lighthearted fantasy.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.08,0:07:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I was introduced to Jack and ended \Nup submitting just the story.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.12,0:07:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My drawings weren't right for a shounen manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.43,0:07:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But she can draw really cute female characters.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.08,0:07:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Aoki will be doing the female \Nfaces and I'll do the rest myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.64,0:07:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm putting my career as a manga \Nartist on the line with this manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.81,0:07:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If this doesn't work out, I'm either going to be \Nan assistant forever or go back to my hometown!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.23,0:07:44.13,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,His career?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.13,0:07:45.73,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,I thought he hadn't even debuted yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.73,0:07:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Although, I didn't expect to be up \Nagainst you guys and Fukuda, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.35,0:07:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.78,0:07:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Fukuda made it in as well?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.53,0:07:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I'm not going to lose.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.95,0:07:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it looks like the editing \Ndepartment is betting on him.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.12,0:07:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.08,0:08:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do they really expect him to be number one?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.08,0:08:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you not heard the order of the stories yet?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.57,0:08:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The order?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.30,0:08:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't even heard the \Nnames of the other entries yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.63,0:08:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a total of four entries.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.72,0:08:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The 37/38 combined issue is \NFukuda Shinta's "Kiyoshi Knight."
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.14,0:08:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Issue 39 is your "Shady Detective Trap."
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.81,0:08:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Issue 40 is our "Hideout Door."
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.56,0:08:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And issue 41 is Makaino Koji's "Colorfusical."
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.73,0:08:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They always run the one they expect to win first.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.03,0:08:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean the order isn't random?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.32,0:08:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes sense if you think about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.63,0:08:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they call it the "Golden Future Cup."
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.76,0:08:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They want the readers to \Nall focus on their top batter.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.87,0:08:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,To name some recent series, "Nurarihyon no Mago"
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.37,0:08:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and "Beelzebub" were both first in \Ntheir lineups and ended up winning.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.21,0:08:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one is in an important spot,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.07,0:08:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm not sure the order after that matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.64,0:08:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure we can win against Fukuda.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.21,0:09:01.18,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,So he doesn't consider us to be competition, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.18,0:09:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I read Fukuda's one-shot.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.14,0:09:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I've seen anything that \Naction-packed or energetic in Jack for a while.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.27,0:09:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it came in seventh.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.80,0:09:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's already good enough \Nto submit for serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.03,0:09:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's reworking it to make it even better,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.41,0:09:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so of course they expect it to do well.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.16,0:09:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't like that story, either.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.91,0:09:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like he's trying to portray \Nhow young people are these days,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.13,0:09:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't think you should use words \Nlike 'drugs' in shounen magazines.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:32.58,0:09:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If he really wants to write something like that, \Nhe should do it in a more mature magazine.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.51,0:09:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.65,0:09:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.17,0:09:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's better to have \Nmore carefree series like yours.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:42.77,0:09:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"Colorfusical" is the one that won honorable \Nmentions in the last Tezuka Awards, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.40,0:09:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.52,0:09:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Makaino Koji.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.44,0:09:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the one
Dialogue: 1,0:09:51.44,0:09:52.73,Sign2,,0,0,0,,{\fnMS PGothic - make\an7\bord0\pos(360,501.389)\fs100.278\blur0.802\c&H1F2827&}Makaino Kouji
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.44,0:09:52.73,Sign2,,0,0,0,,{\fnMS PGothic - make\3c&H9FC7C0&\an7\bord6.685\pos(360,501.389)\fs100.278\blur0.802\c&H1F2827&}Makaino Kouji
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.73,0:09:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with the main character who \Nwas going to change the world
Dialogue: 10,0:09:55.36,0:09:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,by changing the color of objects with his eyes\N and people's hearts with his voice, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.57,0:10:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't care for it that much, but I \Nguess it did well in the questionnaire.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.00,0:10:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought the art was really original, but it felt \Nlike it should be a picture book or a musical.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.67,0:10:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just too surreal.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.71,0:10:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked it.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.96,0:10:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very artistic
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.85,0:10:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and it felt carefree and hopeful.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.47,0:10:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:19.65,0:10:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Manga's got to give people \Ndreams and make them optimistic.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.40,0:10:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like ours does.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.68,0:10:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap, it's already after six.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.35,0:10:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.85,0:10:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we should be leaving.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.52,0:10:31.52,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we'll be right there.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:30.77,0:10:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright then, let's both do our best.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.24,0:10:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.12,0:10:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go too hard on us.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.15,0:10:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, see you later.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.15,0:10:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want my story to lose to somebody like her.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.91,0:10:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And he didn't even pay for our coffee.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.37,0:10:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I am worried about those two, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.58,0:10:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they're going to be strong competition.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.33,0:10:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She was the runner-up in "Story King" and Nakai's \Nbackgrounds and techniques are really good.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.19,0:10:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.79,0:11:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Nakai likes Aoki, don't you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.32,0:11:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it sure seems that way.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.53,0:11:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.82,0:11:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm worried that he'll just end up \Ndoing whatever she tells him to do.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.98,0:11:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, it's none of our business.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:10.68,0:11:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it's her story.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.36,0:11:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the lead, so that shouldn't matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.69,0:11:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.55,0:11:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We should be worrying more about our own story.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.58,0:11:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, you finished another one in under two weeks.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.87,0:11:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The story and the drawings both look good.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.25,0:11:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we should move on \Nto the next chapter, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.38,0:11:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought in an idea I have.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.51,0:11:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.15,0:11:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about you two getting serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.55,0:11:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.42,0:11:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.26,0:11:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.18,0:11:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you got into the "Golden Future Cup," so \Nwe should get you prepared for serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.73,0:11:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean we don't have to do \Na chapter every two weeks anymore?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.90,0:11:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You two have already proven yourselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.52,0:11:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You should start focusing your \Nenergy on getting serialized now.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.53,0:12:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That okay with you?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.56,0:12:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.61,0:12:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.53,0:12:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do our best.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.66,0:12:10.09,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Crap, thinking about not having to draw \Nmakes me realize just how exhausted I am.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:07.16,0:12:11.12,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,The last few weeks must have been tough.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.50,0:12:13.88,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,We finally got permission to do this, \Nso I can't afford to collapse here.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.12,0:12:13.05,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but if we can't do this,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.05,0:12:15.05,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,there's no way we could keep up a serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.63,0:12:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're going to submit our story \Nto the next serialization meeting
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.53,0:12:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,if we get first in the "Golden Future Cup," right?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.88,0:12:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.05,0:12:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming out on top would of course be great,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.40,0:12:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's okay even if you don't get first.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.84,0:12:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.01,0:12:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The questionnaire cards in the issues of Jack \Nthat have "Golden Future Cup" entries in them
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.35,0:12:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,are slightly different than usual.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.97,0:12:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They have an extra option where you \Ncan either 'like' or 'not like' the entry.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.57,0:12:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.98,0:12:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We look at both the story's overall rank \Nand whether or not people say they liked it.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.20,0:12:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Um—
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.42,0:12:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that just for fairness reasons?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.02,0:12:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.57,0:12:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The different entries aren't \Npublished in the same issue,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.08,0:12:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's possible that two series' overall ranks could be the same
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.51,0:12:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or be affected by that issue's \Nregularly running series.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.04,0:12:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we have this other option.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.25,0:13:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if we end up with one series with a \Nhigh 'like' percentage, but a low overall rank
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.55,0:13:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and another with a low 'like' \Npercentage, but a high overall rank,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.51,0:13:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the editing department considers both and \Nhas to decide on which one is the final winner.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.35,0:13:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Um—
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.28,0:13:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.19,0:13:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,About the 'like' percentage—
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.44,0:13:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think the first series to \Nget published is at a big advantage?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.52,0:13:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of readers are just going to \Nbe comparing all the other entries
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.40,0:13:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to the first one to decide on \Nwhether to 'like' or 'dislike' it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.15,0:13:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never really thought about it \Nbefore, but you're probably right.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.04,0:13:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you thought of that so quickly means \Nyou really do have the makings of an excellent writer.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.42,0:13:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can definitely do a solid detective series.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:39.38,0:13:40.92,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Is he lying to me?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.92,0:13:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why you don't \Nnecessarily have to come in first.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:44.97,0:13:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There are plenty of series like "Muhyo and \NRyoji's Bureau of Supernatural Investigation"
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.80,0:13:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that didn't come in first and were still serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.47,0:13:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've only read the names,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.18,0:13:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but to be honest, it's hard to say \Nwhich entry is going to win this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.02,0:13:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,To be frank though,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.73,0:14:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you should think of having an \Nentry in the "Golden Future Cup"
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.65,0:14:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same as getting a one-shot published.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.99,0:14:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If it does well and you have an \Ninteresting name for serialization,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.91,0:14:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll have a chance at getting it serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.45,0:14:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But again, I really do hope you two get first.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.66,0:14:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone else is working hard.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.92,0:14:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,However, nobody else is as prepared \Nfor serialization as you two are.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.50,0:14:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, I absolutely don't want you to \Nlose to something like this "Colorfusical."
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.18,0:14:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"Colorfusical?"
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.93,0:14:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked it.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.89,0:14:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.81,0:14:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, never mind me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.18,0:14:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Just pretend like you didn't hear that.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.89,0:14:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it that good?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.35,0:14:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it really was just me talking to myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.73,0:14:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get first.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.19,0:14:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to get first, get this \Nserialized, and catch up to Niizuma Eiji!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.87,0:14:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Niizuma, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.83,0:14:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He really is a genius.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.91,0:14:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,His popularity is holding steady.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.12,0:15:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,With just his first three volumes, he's \Nalready sold over two million copies.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.66,0:15:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even the editing department \Nthought he'd do this well.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.46,0:15:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The reprintings can't keep up.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.88,0:15:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Two million.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.84,0:15:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The author gets 40 yen for each volume sold.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.01,0:15:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Two million copies at 40 yen each—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.22,0:15:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Woah!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.18,0:15:16.06,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Cut it out.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.06,0:15:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like he's already got \Nan offer for an anime, as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.23,0:15:21.32,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,An anime, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.44,0:15:24.54,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Azuki's already got roles and is doing well, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.94,0:15:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright then.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.86,0:15:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's aim for first place!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.70,0:15:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Saying that I'd be satisfied with \Nanything less was too pessimistic.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.08,0:15:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you guys to catch up to—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.33,0:15:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No, to overtake Niizuma, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.17,0:15:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time you guys brought in a story,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:44.35,0:15:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I told my team leader—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:47.63,0:15:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So how'd it go with that middle school pair?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.88,0:15:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No good, at least for the time being.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.89,0:15:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everybody can be Niizuma Eiji.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.76,0:16:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I think that in three years, they'll have overtaken Niizuma Eiji.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.65,0:16:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I still think the same thing now.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:08.57,0:16:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hattori—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.70,0:16:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We may not make it in three years,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.37,0:16:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but we'll make sure to overtake him someday.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.12,0:16:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's do this.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.50,0:16:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the spirit.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.17,0:16:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Just make sure to put that passion into the story.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.38,0:16:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you're finished, we'll work on \Nfine-tuning your names for serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.55,0:16:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.72,0:16:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I'm sure glad we ended \Nup with Hattori as our editor.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.81,0:16:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.36,0:16:52.74,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Fukuda, the one who the editing \Ndepartment expects to win.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.28,0:16:55.83,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Nakai and Aoki with their amazing art.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.41,0:16:59.92,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,And Makaino Koji with his \Ntotally unique concept.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.87,0:17:02.45,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,We definitely have no shortage of competition.
